node.text: Have you tried our Blue Hen Pilsner yet? This first-state-focused brew started as a brewpub exclusive at our Rehoboth brewpub, and it’s all about celebrating our roots in our home state of Delaware … and lovingly named after our state bird! Check out the video below to learn more from Sam and Brewing Ambassador Bryan about this crisp and refreshing pilsner that we brew with Delmarva grown and malted barley from our friends at @proximity.malt! Blue Hen Pilsner is hitting store shelves now in our Hoppy Variety Pack – try it out and let us know what you think! 🍺🐓💙 #offcentered #craftbeer

node.title: Learn more about Blue Hen Pilsner with Sam & Bryan!

node.text:
It’s the final episode of our ‘Mother Nature, Let’s Do This!’ journey. After weeks of outdoor site visits along the eastern seaboard, Sam & Mariah venture to four remaining spots to see how collective action can have a lasting impact. Watch as Sam and Mariah learn about equitable access efforts at Mianus River Gorge Preserve (@nature.ny) and visit Block Island (@conserve_ma), which @nature_org has deemed one of the “Last Great Places” in the western hemisphere. They cap off the trip with an important conversation on climate policy in Boston, plus an up-close look at the impact of TNC river restoration efforts and the return of alewives to Maine’s waterways. To learn more about ‘Mother Nature, Let’s Do This!’ and our work with TNC, head to dogfish.com/mothernature! 🌱 #MotherNatureLetsDoThis 

*Dogfish Head is a proud supporter of The Nature Conservancy (TNC) and its mission to conserve the lands & waters on which all life depends’ (www.nature.org). TNC does not endorse any specific product, including all those visible in the road trip docuseries. Purchase of Dogfish Head products will not result in a contribution to TNC. node.text: At Dogfish Head, we rely on the goodness of Mother Nature to provide us with the beautiful and bountiful culinary ingredients used in our off-centered beverages and dishes. And with a restless desire to explore at the heart of everything we do, Dogfish Head founders Sam & Mariah Calagione were eager to learn more about the environmental issues facing us globally and on a localized level. So, they packed up and hit the road for a month-long journey in our backyard that is the eastern seaboard. From oyster reefs to the very first @nature_org preserve, we’ve captured it all. Follow along over the coming weeks as we unpack and reflect on an incredible journey. 🌱 #MotherNatureLetsDoThis #conserveandprotect

node.text: It's all in the details! Every beer has a story and every beer label has a story too! Playful and palette-pleasing, Hazy-O!'s maroon and gold packaging features hand-drawn hops and wheat, the “hazy-o” sun setting over the water and a four-ringed bullseye to represent the four oat varieties used in the brewing process! After multiple iterations, countless minute tweaks and a whole lot of patience, our ooohhh-so-creative design team (looking at you, Ryan T.!) hit the bullseye on this label art! 💛🎯 #HazyO #beerisart #craftbeer

node.text: Have you tried our Blue Hen Pilsner yet? This first-state-focused brew started as a brewpub exclusive at our Rehoboth brewpub, and it’s all about celebrating our roots in our home state of Delaware … and lovingly named after our state bird! Check out the video below to learn more from Sam and Brewing Ambassador Bryan about this crisp and refreshing pilsner that we brew with Delmarva grown and malted barley from our friends at @proximity.malt! Blue Hen Pilsner is hitting store shelves now in our Hoppy Variety Pack – try it out and let us know what you think! 🍺🐓💙 #offcentered #craftbeer

It’s the final episode of our ‘Mother Nature, Let’s Do This!’ journey. After weeks of outdoor site visits along the eastern seaboard, Sam & Mariah venture to four remaining spots to see how collective action can have a lasting impact. Watch as Sam and Mariah learn about equitable access efforts at Mianus River Gorge Preserve (@nature.ny) and visit Block Island (@conserve_ma), which @nature_org has deemed one of the “Last Great Places” in the western hemisphere. They cap off the trip with an important conversation on climate policy in Boston, plus an up-close look at the impact of TNC river restoration efforts and the return of alewives to Maine’s waterways. To learn more about ‘Mother Nature, Let’s Do This!’ and our work with TNC, head to dogfish.com/mothernature! 🌱 #MotherNatureLetsDoThis
